<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 7:44PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Anson
and south central Richmond Counties through 845 PM EDT...
At 743 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Rockingham, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Hamlet, Dobbins Heights, East Rockingham, Diggs and
Blewett Falls Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is also occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
